.TH simple_shell "2024-04-23" "version 1.0" "User Manuals"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple shell interface to execute commands.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [option] ...

.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a simple UNIX command interpreter written in C that replicates functionalities of the sh (Bourne Shell). It can execute commands read from the standard input or from a file.

.SH OPTIONS
There are no options available for simple_shell. All interactions are handled interactively or non-interactively through standard input.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
:.BI Prompt
Displays "simple_shell " when ready to accept a command in interactive mode.
.TP
.BI Command execution
Executes commands entered by the user or read from a script.
.TP
.BI Built-in commands:
The shell supports the following built-in commands:
.TP
.BI "env"
Prints the current environment variables.
.TP
.BI "exit"
Exits the shell.
.TP
.BI Path handling
Automatically resolves commands using the PATH environment variable.
.TP
.BI Error handling
Prints relevant errors to stderr if commands fail to execute or are not found.
.SH USAGE
To start the shell in interactive mode, just type:
.nf
$ ./simple_shell
.fi
You can also redirect input from a file:
.nf
$ ./simple_shell < script_file
.fi
